A third-year law student from Walter Sisulu has died after being beaten by other students. Songezo Takezi and an unknown man were severely beaten by other students after being accused of stealing from the university residence. The Daily Dispatch reported that the 23-year-old Takezi is the third student this year to have been killed on campus. Earlier this year Lwando Mantshontsho 27-year-old final year medical student was stabbed to death. Mantshotsho was stabbed after he was parting with another student on campus. TNA Reporter  